
===================================
📌 1. Finglish Version (Persian Latin Script)
===================================

📖 **Tashrih:**
    Dastoor `desktop-file-validate` baraye check kardane dorosti va standard boodane file-haye `.desktop` estefade mishavad. File-haye `.desktop` baraye ijade shortcut ha dar menu-ha va desktop dar Linux be kar miravand.

⚙️ **Gozine-ha:**
    🔹 `<file.desktop>`  --> 🎯 Esme file `.desktop` ke bayad check shavad.
    🔹 `--warn-as-error`  --> 🚨 Agar khata ya warning peyda shod, an ra be عنوان error نشان بده.
    🔹 `--version` --> ℹ️ Namayeshe version barname.

🛠 **Mesal-ha:**

    $ desktop-file-validate myapp.desktop

    🔹 Check kardane dorosti file `myapp.desktop`.

    $ desktop-file-validate --warn-as-error myapp.desktop

    🔹 Agar file `myapp.desktop` error dasht, command ba error code kharej mishavad.

✅ **Mesal sade:**

    $ desktop-file-validate mygame.desktop

    🔹 Agar file `mygame.desktop` moshkeli nadashte bashad, chizi chap nemishavad. Agar moshkeli dashte bashad, khata ya warning namayesh dade mishavad.

===================================
📌 2. English Version
===================================

📖 **Description:**
    The `desktop-file-validate` command is used to check the validity and standardization of `.desktop` files. `.desktop` files are used to create shortcuts in menus and on the desktop in Linux.

⚙️ **Options:**
    🔹 `<file.desktop>`  --> 🎯 The name of the `.desktop` file to be checked.
    🔹 `--warn-as-error`  --> 🚨 Treat warnings as errors, causing the command to exit with an error code if any warnings are found.
    🔹 `--version` --> ℹ️ Display program version.

🛠 **Examples:**

    $ desktop-file-validate myapp.desktop

    🔹 Check the validity of the `myapp.desktop` file.

    $ desktop-file-validate --warn-as-error myapp.desktop

    🔹 If the `myapp.desktop` file has errors, the command will exit with an error code.

✅ **Simple Example:**

    $ desktop-file-validate mygame.desktop

    🔹 If the `mygame.desktop` file has no issues, nothing will be printed. If there are problems, errors or warnings will be displayed.
